      "published": "Fri, 24 Jul 2026 12:09:57 +0000",
      "summary_raw": "<p>WAN-IFRA denounces spurious claims of ‘unjust vexation’ targeting colleague Marchel Espina and calls for all charges against the journalist to be dropped.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/worlds-press-condemns-arrest-of-philippine-journalist-marchel-espina/\">World’s press condemns arrest of Philippine journalist Marchel Espina</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org\">WAN-IFRA</a>.</p>",
      "source": "WAN-IFRA"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://wan-ifra.org/?p=118136",
      "title": "New report: Deep dives from World News Media Congress 2026",
      "link": "https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/new-report-deep-dives-from-world-news-media-congress-2026/",
      "published": "Fri, 24 Jul 2026 12:09:50 +0000",
      "summary_raw": "<p>WAN-IFRA just published its World News Media Congress 2026 Report, which distills the key takeaways from our event in Marseille, focusing heavily on industry resilience, AI’s growing impact on news, the need for collaboration, and reshaping the value exchange between publishers and tech platforms.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/new-report-deep-dives-from-world-news-media-congress-2026/\">New report: Deep dives from World News Media Congress 2026</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org\">WAN-IFRA</a>.</p>",
      "source": "WAN-IFRA"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://wan-ifra.org/?p=118033",
      "title": "What AI can’t replace: Five lessons from the Future Newsrooms Study",
      "link": "https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/what-ai-cant-replace-five-lessons-from-the-future-newsrooms-study/",
      "published": "Fri, 24 Jul 2026 10:13:01 +0000",
      "summary_raw": "<p>Journalism's top thinkers on newsroom innovation unpack what sets journalism apart in a corrupted information ecosystem.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/what-ai-cant-replace-five-lessons-from-the-future-newsrooms-study/\">What AI can&#8217;t replace: Five lessons from the Future Newsrooms Study</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org\">WAN-IFRA</a>.</p>",
      "source": "WAN-IFRA"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://wan-ifra.org/?p=118087",
      "title": "‘Forced maturity’: The year Ukraine’s newsrooms stopped waiting for donor funding to save them",
      "link": "https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/forced-maturity-the-year-ukraines-newsrooms-stopped-waiting-for-donor-funding-to-save-them/",
      "published": "Fri, 24 Jul 2026 10:11:09 +0000",
      "summary_raw": "<p>Collapsing USAID, mobilisation pressure, and sheer exhaustion made 2025 the toughest year on record for Ukraine's regional media, the Media Development Foundation's latest study found. But the crisis also pushed a donor-dependent sector to finally test what sustainability without grants might look like.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/forced-maturity-the-year-ukraines-newsrooms-stopped-waiting-for-donor-funding-to-save-them/\">&#8216;Forced maturity&#8217;: The year Ukraine&#8217;s newsrooms stopped waiting for donor funding to save them</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org\">WAN-IFRA</a>.</p>",
      "source": "WAN-IFRA"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://wan-ifra.org/?p=117913",
      "title": "How you can take part in World News Day 2026",
      "link": "https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/how-you-can-take-part-in-world-news-day-2026/",
      "published": "Thu, 23 Jul 2026 16:00:32 +0000",
      "summary_raw": "<p>The challenges facing journalism are no longer predictions about the future – they are our daily reality, and they are intensifying. But something else is intensifying too: the need for trusted journalism and our solidarity.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org/2026/07/how-you-can-take-part-in-world-news-day-2026/\">How you can take part in World News Day 2026</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://wan-ifra.org\">WAN-IFRA</a>.</p>",
      "source": "WAN-IFRA"
    },
    {
